The paper deals with the secrecy capacity of classical-quantum wiretap channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the use of various resources such as randomness, common randomness, and correlation, which are relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and coding theory (cs.CC). The concept of super-activation is related to multi-user information theory (cs.MM), and the analysis of different types of resources can also be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI).
